1. First install the vmbuilder package > (python-vm-builder 0.12.4+bzr464-0ubuntu1)
2. Make sure the .conf files contain the right path to the firsboot.sh
3. Build the image with vmbuilder.
4. Then execute ./afterbuild.sh <appname>
5. Start the vm in the vmware player.
6. After boot remove the /etc/udev/rules.d/70-persistent-net-rules and halt the vm.
7. Then execute ./cleanup.sh <appname>
8. Then execute ./package.sh <appname>
9. Sign the package with the gpg key.
10. Upload to openapp/vmware directory
11. ????
12. PROFIT
